<reference id="step" xml:lang="en-us">
   <title>
      <keyword>step</keyword>
   </title>
   <shortdesc>The &lt;<keyword>step</keyword>&gt; element represents an action that
a user must follow to accomplish a task. Each step in a task must contain
a command &lt;<keyword>cmd</keyword>&gt; element which describes
the particular action the user must do to accomplish the overall task. The
step element can also contain information &lt;<keyword>info</keyword>&gt;, substeps
&lt;<keyword>substeps</keyword>&gt;, tutorial information &lt;<keyword>tutorialinfo</keyword>&gt;,
a step example &lt;<keyword>stepxmp</keyword>&gt;, choices &lt;<keyword>choices</keyword>&gt;
or a stepresult &lt;<keyword>stepresult</keyword>&gt;, although these are optional.</shortdesc>
